    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4181" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ζωστήρ</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῆρος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ζώννῡμι</span>): (1)
          warrior's <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">body-girdle</span>, of leather strengthened with
          metal plates, which covered the lower part of the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θώρηξ</span>, and the upper part of the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μίτρη</span> and of the <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ζῶμα</span> (see cuts Nos. 3 and 79). (Il.) —(2)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">girdle</span> worn over the tunic, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.72</span></i>. (See cut No. 73.)</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
